## Tasks [/tasks]

### addTask.php [POST /addTask.php]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Attributes
        + description: Description (string, required) - Description of the task
        + due_date: 1265412302 (number, required) - Due date of the task as Unix timestamp
        + `user_id`: 1 (number) - Id of the user (is required if team_id is not used)
        + `team_id`: 2 (number) - Id of the team (is required if user_id is not used)
        + task_type_id: 3 (number, required) - Category of the task
        + duration: 120 (number, required) - Amount of mintues that should be spent on the task
        + priority: A (enum[string], required) - Priority of the task
            + Members
                + A
                + B
                + C
                + D
        + for: company (enum[string]) - Who this task should be billed to
            + Members
                + contact
                + company
                + project_milestone
        + for_id: 4 (number) - The id of who this task should be billed to
        + creator_user_id: 5 (number) - Id the user that created the task
        + related_deal_id: 6 (number) - Id of the deal related to the task
        + related_ticket_id: 7 (number) - Id of the ticket related to the task
        + custom_field_<id>: 6 (number) - Where <id> is an custom field id

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        29

### updateTask.php [POST /updateTask.php]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Attributes
        + task_id: 1 (number, required) - Id of the task
        + description: Description (string) - Description of the task
        + duration: 120 (number) - Amount of mintues that should be spent on the task
        + task_type_id: 3 (number) - Category of the task
        + priority: A (enum[string]) - Priority of the task
            + Members
                + A
                + B
                + C
                + D
        + done: 0 (enum[number]) - Done state of the task
            + Members
                + 0
                + 1
        + custom_field_<id>: 6 (number, optional) - Where <id> is an custom field id

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        "OK"

